llectual pursuit can-and must-be open to all.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMathematicsxPhilosophy2DE-289. 0aMathematicsxPhilosophy. 0aMathematicsxSocial aspects. 7aMATHEMATICS / History & Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aJackson, Christopher.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2020 Englishz978311070484608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2020z9783110704662oZDB-23-DMA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069231040uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300248814?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300248814423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300248814/original  a978-3-11-069231-0  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070484-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DMAb2020